aa(lp9
VThis week, there have been a whole slew and deluge of stories
p10
aVcoming out from the leak of 11 million documents
p11
aVfrom a Panamanian-based law firm called Mossack Fonseca.
p12
aVThe release of these papers from Panama lifts the veil on a tiny piece
p13
aVof the secretive offshore world.
p14
aVWe get an insight into how clients and banks and lawyers
p15
aVgo to companies like Mossack Fonseca
p16
aVand say, "OK, we want an anonymous company,
p17
aVcan you give us one?"
p18
aVSo you actually get to see the emails,
p19
aVyou get to see the exchanges of messages,
p20
aVyou get to see the mechanics of how this works,
p21
aVhow this operates.
p22
aa(lp23
VNow, this has already started to have pretty immediate repercussions.
p24
aVThe Prime Minister of Iceland has resigned.
p25
aVWe've also had news
p26
aVthat an ally of the brutal Syrian dictator Bashar Al-Assad
p27
aVhas also got offshore companies.
p28
aVThere's been allegations of a $2 billion money trail
p29
aVthat leads back to President Vladimir Putin of Russia
p30
aVvia his close childhood friend,
p31
aVwho happens to be a top cellist.
p32
aVAnd there will be a lot of rich individuals out there
p33
aVand others who will be nervous about the next set of stories
p34
aVand the next set of leaked documents.
p35
aa(lp36
VNow, this sounds like the plot of a spy thriller
p37
aVor a John Grisham novel.
p38
aVIt seems very distant from you, me, ordinary people.
p39
aVWhy should we care about this?
p40
aVBut the truth is that if rich and powerful individuals
p41
aVare able to keep their money offshore
p42
aVand not pay the taxes that they should,
p43
aVit means that there is less money for vital public services
p44
aVlike healthcare, education, roads.
p45
aVAnd that affects all of us.
p46
aa(lp47
VNow, for my organization Global Witness,
p48
aVthis exposé has been phenomenal.
p49
aVWe have the world's media and political leaders
p50
aVtalking about how individuals can use offshore secrecy
p51
aVto hide and disguise their assets \u2014
p52
aVsomething we have been talking about and exposing for a decade.
p53
aa(lp54
VNow, I think a lot of people find this entire world baffling and confusing,
p55
aVand hard to understand how this sort of offshore world works.
p56
aVI like to think of it a bit like a Russian doll.
p57
aVSo you can have one company stacked inside another company,
p58
aVstacked inside another company,
p59
aVmaking it almost impossible to really understand
p60
aVwho is behind these structures.
p61
aVIt can be very difficult for law enforcement
p62
aVor tax authorities, journalists, civil society
p63
aVto really understand what's going on.
